@node "COPY" "SN Maint Record v1.1 - Copyright/Registration"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Maint Record v1.1 - Copyright/Registration
└───────────────────────────────────────────────┘

This software is subject to the "Standard Amiga FD-Software Copyright
Note".  It is MAILWARE as defined in paragraph 4s for non-programming
CNet SysOps.  For CNet SysOps who author their own software, it is
additionally defined as KEYWARE, meaning if the software requires
registration and/or a keyfile, you must "swap" registration with me.
(i.e. I give you a registered copy of MY software in exchange for a
registered copy of YOUR software.)  For more information, please read
the file, "AFD-COPYRIGHT" (Version 1 or higher), included in this
archive.

As defined in the AFD-COPYRIGHT, you are requested to send me a bit
of mail if you find use for this program.

Note that there is only one version of this program, not a special
one or uncrippled version for those who send me mail.  Also, this is
NOT a crippled version.  Updates, bug-fixes and further releases of
this program is dependent on the perceived need/usage of this program
as determined by the amount of mail I receive regarding it.

Please send all correspondence to the address below for snail mail:

                        Phil Beazley
                  c/o Autumn's Harvest Inn
                    II MEF G-5, 2d SRIG
                       PSC Box 20085
                 Camp Lejeune, NC 28542-0085

Or, for email, use beazleyp@mqg-smtp3.usmc.mil!

This and future versions will be available for download from Aminet
and also from other SN PFile @{"Support Sites" link "SUPPORT"}.  To get a list
of all currently available and up-to-date SN PFiles, see the included
SN_Files.txt and SN_FilesInfo.txt or request info via email.

Suggestions are welcome!  Bug reports are mandatory!  :)

Beta-testers are needed for this and other SN PFiles.  Please send me
netmail if interested.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
@node "INFO" "SN Maint Record v1.1 - Information"
@toc "MAIN"
┌────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Maint Record v1.1 - Information
└────────────────────────────────────┘

Sometimes it's hard to keep track of all the modifications you've made to
the system.  I made this so I could "jot" down what I did whenever I made
any changes.  It's also handy for users to view so they can see what's going
on with the BBS.

Features:
  - Only you (and other level 31 users) can add or reset the list.
  - Your users can, if you wish, view the maint record.

NOTE:  This is a compiled ARexx script.  However, it does not require any
       additional libraries or RPStart to function (unless otherwise
       noted in these docs).

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
