@node "INSTALL" "SN Maint Record v1.1 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Maint Record v1.1 - Installation Procedures
└────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  Run the included installation script either of the following
    two ways:

    a.  Type "Installer Install_MaintRec" from the Shell.

    b.  Click on the "Install_MaintRec" icon from Workbench.

 2  The installation script moves the required files to your specified
    location and creates an environment variable pointing to that
    directory.

 3  Add "BMR |{#4PFiles:SN_MaintRec %23}" to your bbsmenu under the
    "#1; Maintenance menu" heading if you only want yourself and others
    with maintenance access to view it or under "#2; Available everywhere"
    or "#3; Main prompt" if you want everyone to be able to view it.

    Regardless of which location used, only those with access level 31
    can add to it or reset it.

    Note that the above { is actually a control-Q command and be sure to
    modify the paths to reflect your setup!

 4  Reload your bbstext/bbsmenu via CNet's Control Panel menu (option
    #3, "Text/menu reload  RAmiga-T" and you're all set!

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
@node "BUGS" "SN Maint Record v1.1 - Bugs/Problems"
@toc "MAIN"
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Maint Record v1.1 - Bugs/Problems
└──────────────────────────────────────┘

  - No known bugs at this point.  This has been in operation for at least
    four years now, probably a little more.  Except for some code clean-up,
    nothing has really changed, so it should be very stable.  I've never
    had any problems with it.  If you see anything fishy, let me know!

    Thanks!

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
